{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "chinese-phil-expert",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Agree Option B — terminology is reference, not narrative",
    "content": "**Agree with Option B.**\n\nThe Preface's narrative sections (On the Title, Reinterpretation of 形) already introduce the two most critical terms — Jing and the metaphysical/metaphysics distinction — organically within their philosophical context. The remaining terminology entries (constancy, the non-rational, the Poetic, dreamscape, vain presumption, the Dao-De sequence, Three Realities) are reference material that readers will consult when they encounter the terms, not absorb cover-to-cover before Essay 1; that is glossary behavior, and it belongs adjacent to the glossary.\n\nAlso agree with both smaller trims (working-draft paragraph, forward references). Ready to implement all three changes on your word."
  }
}
